<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1445,1831]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Newly recorded in New Brunswick. 
<taxonomicName box="[655,872,1685,1710]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Amara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="neoscotica">
<emphasis box="[655,872,1685,1710]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Amara neoscotica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described from Halifax, Nova 
<collectingCountry box="[151,224,1725,1751]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Scotia</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Casey" box="[275,439,1725,1751]" pageId="8" pageNumber="34" refString="Casey, T. L. (1924) Memoirs on the Coleoptera XI. Lancaster Press, Lancaster, Pennsylvania. 347 pp." type="book" year="1924">
Casey (
<number box="[366,430,1725,1751]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1924.0">1924</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. It was subsequently synonymized by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lindroth" box="[908,1099,1725,1751]" pageId="8" pageNumber="34" refString="Lindroth, C. H. (1954) Carabid beetles from Nova Scotia. The Canadian Entomologist, 86, 299 - 310." type="journal article" year="1954">
Lindroth (
<number box="[1030,1091,1725,1751]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1954.0">1954</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
with 
<taxonomicName authority="Putzeys" authorityName="Putzeys" box="[1172,1436,1725,1751]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Amara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cupreolata">
<emphasis box="[1172,1334,1725,1750]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">A. cupreolata</emphasis>
Putzeys
</taxonomicName>
before being restored as a distinct species by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hieke" box="[703,865,1765,1791]" pageId="8" pageNumber="34" refString="Hieke, F. (2003) Die Gruppe der Amara (Amara) cupreolata Putzeys 1866 (Coleoptera: Carabidae). Linzer Biologische Beitrage. 35 (1), 201 - 216." type="journal article" year="2003">
Hieke (
<number box="[792,856,1765,1791]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2003.0">2003</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Recorded in northeastern North 
<collectingCountry box="[1268,1369,1765,1791]" name="United States of America" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">America</collectingCountry>
from Nova 
<collectingCountry box="[221,297,1805,1831]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Scotia</collectingCountry>
, Ontario, Québec, and Vermont (
<bibRefCitation author="Hieke" box="[683,827,1805,1831]" pageId="8" pageNumber="34" refString="Hieke, F. (2003) Die Gruppe der Amara (Amara) cupreolata Putzeys 1866 (Coleoptera: Carabidae). Linzer Biologische Beitrage. 35 (1), 201 - 216." type="journal article" year="2003">
Hieke 
<number box="[763,827,1805,1831]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2003.0">2003</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
